#. type: Title =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/assessments-certification.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Assessment and certification"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/assessments-certification.adoc:6
msgid ""
"In this module, you will review the criteria to be used to assess "
"assignments and to achieve certification."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/assessments-certification.adoc:9
msgid ""
"Upon completion of the course and successful submission and assessment of "
"assignments (by trainers), participants have the opportunity to earn a "
"digital certification https://openbadgefactory.com/en/about-open-badges/"
"[Open Badges]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/assessments-certification.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "An overall score of 2.5-2.9 earns a BASIC Biodiversity Data Mobilization badge"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/assessments-certification.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::basic.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/assessments-certification.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "An overall score of 3.0-4.0 earns an ADVANCED Biodiversity Data Mobilization badge"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/assessments-certification.adoc:16
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::advanced.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/assessments-certification.adoc:19
msgid ""
"Participants are required to submit (in English) a choice of two Use Cases "
"and each Use Case is scored against the educational rubrics for the course. "
"The rubrics define the skills and performance levels on which the learning "
"objectives for the course are built."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/assessments-certification.adoc:20
msgid ""
"Review the rubrics to ensure understanding of the skills that will be "
"assessed for certification."
msgstr ""
